      "english": "{0:Firmly established}, {1:firmly fixed}: he {8:whose} {7:prajñā} {2:‘I} {3:am} {5:Brahman}, {4:the Supreme}{6:’} is {10:the man of settled wisdom}. {13:What} is the {14:‘speech’} {11:of} {12:such a one} — {15:what} {16:saying}, {17:utterance}? {18:How} {21:is he described} {20:by others} — {22:of one settled in samādhi}, {24:established} {23:in absorption}, {25:O} {26:Keśava}? {30:Or} what does the {27:steady-minded one}, {28:the man of settled wisdom}, {29:himself} {31:} {32:say}? {33:} {34:How does he sit}, {35:how does he move}? {36:What is} {37:his sitting}, {38:his walking}, {39:or} {41:how} is it with {40:him}? — {42:thus} {43:is the meaning}. {45:The marks} {44:of the man of settled wisdom}, {46:by this} {47:verse}, {48:are asked}.",
