      "english": "{0:Moreover}{1:}: {6:the sage} {5:who}, {2:in all bodies}, {3:in life and the rest}, {4:even}, {7:is without affection} — that {20:‘affection’} (sneha) is {18:a tāmasic} {19:particular modification}, {17:a synonym of love} {16:directed elsewhere}, {8:in which} {9:being present} {11:loss and gain} {10:belonging to another} {13:are superimposed} {12:upon oneself}; {14:he}, {15:being such}, {21:in every way} {22:devoid of it}, is {23:‘without affection’}. {26:But} {24:toward the Lord}, {25:the Supreme Self}, he {29:should} {27:indeed} {28:have affection} {27:in every way}{30:}; for {31:the absence of affection toward the non-Self} is {32:for that very purpose}, {34:it should be understood}{33:}. On {39:gaining} {36:this auspicious} {38:object}, {37:a cause of pleasure}, {35:procured by this or that commenced karma}, he does {40:not} {41:rejoice} — does not, {42:with elation}, {44:praise} it{43:}. On {48:gaining} {45:the inauspicious}, {46:a cause of pain}, {47:object}, he does {49:not} {50:revile} — does not, {51:with inner spite}, {53:censure} it{52:}. {55:For} {54:in the ignorant}, {56:the auspicious object that is a cause of pleasure}, {58:such as one’s own wife}, {57:which} {59:— that} {60:auspicious} {61:object} {62:prompts the praising of its qualities} — {63:a mental modification} {65:of praising}, {64:a deluded rejoicing}; {66:and that} {67:is} {68:tāmasic}, {71:being purposeless} {70:since the praising of its qualities} {69:serves no inducement of another}. {72:Likewise} {78:the inauspicious} {79:object} — {75:another’s superior learning and the like}, {74:a cause of pain} {73:by generating envy} {77:toward} {76:him} — {80:prompts a deluded mental modification of censuring it}{81:} {82:a particular mental modification}; {83:that} {84:too} {85:is tāmasic}, {88:being purposeless} {87:since the censure} {86:of it} {87:serves no warding-off}. {89:Those two}, {90:rejoicing and dveṣa}, {91:being of the nature of error} {92:and tāmasic}, {93:how} could they {97:occur} {96:in the} {94:unerring} {96:sthita-prajña} {95:established in pure sattva}? {98:Therefore}, {99:since there is nothing to perturb him}, for {100:that} {103:sage} {101:who is without affection}, {102:devoid of elation and dejection}, {104:the prajñā} {105:whose object is the truth of the Supreme Self} {106:stands firm}, {107:culminating in its fruit} — {108:he} is {109:the sthita-prajña}, {111:that is the sense}{110:}. {112:And} {114:too} {113:any other} {115:seeker of release} {116:everywhere} {118:should be} {117:without affection}, {120:on gaining} {119:the auspicious} {121:should} {122:not} {121:praise} nor {126:censure} {124:on gaining} {123:the inauspicious}{125:}{127:}, is {128:the import}. {129:And here} {130:too} {136:the exclusion} {137:is stated}, {135:namely} that {133:he would not} {134:utter} {132:words} {131:of the form of censure, praise and the like}.",
