      "sanskrit": "yatataḥ prayatnaṃ kurvataḥ hi yasmāt kaunteya puruṣasya vipaścitaḥ medhāvino 'pi iti vyavahitena saṃbandhaḥ | indriyāṇi pramāthīni pramathana-śīlāni viṣayābhimukhaṃ hi puruṣaṃ vikṣobhayanti ākulīkurvanti, ākulīkṛtya ca haranti prasabhaṃ prasahya prakāśam eva paśyato viveka-vijñāna-yuktaṃ manaḥ",
      "ourRendering": "Of one striving — making effort — ‘hi’ (for), since; O son of Kuntī, of a man, even of one who is wise, discerning — the construction connects across the intervening words. The senses, churning and agitating, of a churning nature — for they violently agitate, throw into turmoil, a man turned toward the objects, and, having thrown him into turmoil, they carry off by force, overpowering him, in open view indeed, the mind of one who is looking on, the mind endowed with discriminative knowledge.",
