      "locus": "2.61",
      "sanskrit": "tāni sarvāṇi saṃyamya saṃyamanaṃ vaśīkaraṇaṃ kṛtvā yuktaḥ samāhitaḥ san āsīta mat-paro 'haṃ vāsudevaḥ sarva-pratyag-ātmā paro yasya sa mat-paraḥ, nānyo 'haṃ tasmāt ity āsīta ity arthaḥ | evam āsīnasya yater vaśe hi yasyendriyāṇi vartante abhyāsa-balāt tasya prajñā pratiṣṭhitā",
      "ourRendering": "Reining in all of them, having effected the reining in, the bringing under control, yoked, composed, being so, let him sit ‘intent on Me’ — ‘I, Vāsudeva, the inmost Self of all, am the Supreme of whom’: he is ‘intent on Me’, ‘I am no other than That’ — so let him sit, that is the meaning. Thus for such a seated ascetic, in whose control the senses abide by the force of practice, his prajñā stands firm.",
