      "english": "{0:If it be so}, {1:then} {2:there} {3:what} is {4:the remedy}? {6:To that} {7:He says} {8:‘tāni’} {9:—}. {14:Reining in}, {15:bringing under control}, {12:all} {10:those} {11:senses}, {13:which are the instruments of knowledge and karma}, {16:yoked}, {17:composed}, {18:of restrained mind}, {19:being so}, {20:let him sit}, {22:let him abide} {21:free of activity}. {24:How} is {25:the bringing under control} {23:of the churning ones} to be had? — {26:so}, {27:if one asks} — {28:to that} {29:He says} {30:‘mat-paraḥ’}: {32:I}, {33:the Self of all}, {34:Vāsudeva} {35:alone}, am {36:the Supreme}, {37:the most excellent}, {38:the one to be sought}, {39:of whom} — {40:he} is {41:‘intent on Me’}, {42:the one-pointed devotee of Mine}, {43:that is} {44:the meaning}. {45:And so} {46:too} {47:it has been stated}, {48:‘For} {49:the devotees of Vāsudeva} there is {52:never} {50:anything inauspicious} {51:found}.’ {54:Just as}, {55:indeed}, {56:in the world}, {60:robbers}, {59:having taken refuge with} {57:a strong} {58:king}, {61:are subdued} — {66:and} {65:knowing} {63:‘this one} is {62:sheltered by the king’} {64:—} {67:they themselves} {68:very} {70:become} {69:subject to him} — {71:so} {72:too}, {75:having taken refuge with} {73:the Lord}, {74:the inner controller of all}, {76:by His} {77:very} power are {78:the wicked} {79:senses} {80:to be subdued}; {81:and} {82:again}, {86:thinking} {84:‘this one} is {83:sheltered by the Lord’} {85:—}, {87:they} {90:become} {88:subject to him} {89:indeed} {91:—} this is {92:the import}. {94:And} {93:as for how} {96:great is the power} {95:of devotion to the Lord} — {97:that} {98:at length} {99:later} {100:we will explain}. {103:He states} {102:the fruit} {101:of the senses’ mastery} by {104:’vaśe} {105:hi’} {106:—} {107:it is clear}. {108:Thus}, by {109:this} ‘{111:being} {110:one whose senses have been brought under control}, {112:let him sit}’, {113:so} {118:the answer} {117:to the question} ‘{114:how} {115:does he sit}’ {120:comes to be} {119:stated}{116:.}",
