      "sanskrit": "tarhyaśaktyānyevetyata āha – tānīti| bahuyatnavataḥ śakyāni| ato yatnaṃ kuryādityāśayaḥ| yukto – mayi manoyuktaḥ| ahameva paraḥ sarvasmādutkṛṣṭo yasya sa matparaḥ| phalamāha – vaśe hīti",
      "ourRendering": "‘Then it is the other ones alone that are unconquerable, through want of strength’ — to that He says ‘tāni’: they are masterable by one of much effort; hence let him make the effort, that is the intent. ‘yoked’ — with the mind joined to Me. ‘I alone am the Supreme’, the most excellent above all, of whom — he is ‘intent on Me’. He states the fruit by ‘vaśe hi’.",
