      "english": "{3:It was said} ‘{1:he attains} {0:serenity}’; now {7:what} {8:would come to be} {6:when} {5:serenity} exists is {10:stated} with the word {11:“on serenity”}. {16:When there is} {14:serenity} {13:of the mind}, {15:of the form of limpidity}, {24:there arises} {22:for that} {23:ascetic} {20:the destruction}, {21:the cessation}, {17:of all sorrows} — {18:the personal and the rest}, {19:the play of ignorance}. {25:For}, {26:since}, {27:of the serene-minded} {28:ascetic}, {32:the understanding} {33:in the form of the unity of Brahman and the Self} {29:quickly}, {30:swiftly}, {31:verily}, {34:comes to abide all around} — {35:around}, {36:on all sides}, {37:abides}, {39:becomes} {38:firm} — {40:since the obstacle of contrary conviction and the like is absent}. {41:And} {42:thence}: {44:when} {43:serenity} exists there is {45:the standing-firm of the understanding}; {46:thence} {47:the cessation of the ignorance opposed to it}; {48:thence} {49:the destruction of all its effect, sorrow} — {50:so}, {52:even} {51:in this sequence}, {53:in serenity}, {56:the statement that it is a destroyer of all sorrow}, {55:for the sake of magnifying} {54:the ascetic}, {58:is no} {59:contradiction}.",
