      "english": "{0:But surely}, {2:in the absence of sight} {1:toward objects}, {3:how} {4:does he} {6:enjoy} {5:them}? {7:Thus} {8:expecting this}, {9:He says}, {11:} {10:‘āpūryamāṇam’}. {23:Just as} into {18:the sea}, {13:though filled} {12:by various streams and rivers} {14:yet} {15:‘unmoving in its station’}, {16:not overstepping its bound}{17:,} {21:other} {22:waters} {19:again} {20:also} {24:enter}, {25:so} {26:the kāmas}, {27:the objects}, {37:enter} {29:the sage} {28:whom}, {30:of inward sight}, {32:who is unmodified} {31:by the enjoyments}{33:,} {35:drawn in} {34:by commenced karma}, {36:being}; {38:he} {41:attains} {39:peace}, {40:isolation (kaivalya)}. {42:But not} {44:the kāma-desirer}, {45:whose nature is the craving for enjoyment}.",
