      "english": "{0:This} {1:aforesaid} {2:Brahman-state} — {4:being} {3:in Brahman} — {5:this} {6:standing}: {12:the abiding} {10:in the very form of Brahman} {11:itself}, {9:having renounced} {7:all} {8:karma} — {13:that} {14:is what it is}. {15:O} {16:Pārtha}, {20:having attained}, {21:having gained}, {18:this} {19:state}, one {22:is not} {23:deluded}, {24:does not} {26:come to} {25:delusion}. {27:Having stood firm} {28:in this}, {30:in the Brahman-state} {29:standing}, {31:the aforesaid}, {33:even} {32:at the final time}, {36:even} {34:in the last} {35:age}, one {40:reaches}, {41:goes to}, {37:brahma-nirvāṇa}, {38:the blowing-out-into-Brahman, its repose}, {39:liberation}. {42:What} {43:indeed} {44:is to be said} of one who, {47:having renounced} {45:from the stage of studentship} {46:itself}, {48:life-long} {49:who} {52:abides} {50:in Brahman} {51:alone} — {53:he} {55:reaches} {54:brahma-nirvāṇa} {56:thus}.",
